    "created_at": "2024-03-06T23:46:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-03-06T23:46:06Z",
    "body": "> Probably easiest to say: X is more specific than Y so if X is there then don't show Y. That would pre-empt any debates between pnpm/yarn/bun etc.\r\n\r\nMy problem with this is that you're lumping Bun in with pnpm and yarn. Bun is a JavaScript runtime first and a package manager second. Like Deno, it's meant to replace Node.js, you do not need Node.js installed to use Bun.\r\n",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
    "reactions": {
      "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/starship/starship/issues/comments/1982056048/reactions",
